tire_price_explanation: Please enter the replacement price for steer, drive and trailer tires respectively. Here’s why: without  a tire price, we can’t calculate your annual tire costs and cost savings.
tire_runout_miles_explanation: Please enter the tire runout miles in the respective fields below.  Here’s how we define runout miles: the measurement (in miles) from when your tires are mounted to when your tires are taken out of service. Runout miles are necessary to help calculate your annual cost-per-mile. And after we calculate your annual cost-per-mile, graphical summaries will be provided in the executive summary to help visualize the impact of runout miles and annual costs.
tire_runout_kilometers_explantion: Please enter the tire runout kilometers in the respective fields below.  Here’s how we define runout kilometers: the measurement (in kilometers) from when your tires are mounted to when your tires are taken out of service. Runout kilometers are necessary to help calculate your annual cost-per-kilometer. And after we calculate your annual cost-per-kilometer, graphical summaries will be provided in the executive summary to help visualize the impact of runout kilometers and annual costs.
first _life_explanation: Compare your current tires to a proposed set of tires.
second_life_explantion: If you click on the second life tab, you will have the ability to consider the second life of a tire, including retreads. The second life tab can be helpful if you are running a mix of new tires and retreads in your operation.
blended_average_explanation: Customize your results using the blended average tab. The blended average tab allows you to customize the simulation based on your mix of first life and second life simulations. After you have completed your first life and second life simulations, a mix of 50%/50% is the default, but it’s easy to modify those numbers to fit your operation.
weight_savings_explanation: If MICHELIN X One tires are selected in the first life configuration, you will be asked if you would like to calculate the potential weight savings.  We will ask you to provide a few more details about what you haul, so you can receive a customized view of the potential impacts of increased payload and increased revenue.  The weight savings tab is optional and does not have to be selected to complete the simulation.
rolling_explanation: The base rolling resistance will always be 100 for your Current Tires configuration. The 100 baseline measurement serves as a reference for each tire and the entire vehicle configuration.
weight_savings_page_explanation: Want to see how much more payload you can haul by switching to MICHELIN Xone  tires? Please provide a few more details to calculate your potential weight savings and estimate additional revenue from hauling more payload.
additional_revenue_weight_savings: Would you like to calculate additional revenue from weight savings
